# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version is
#   defined in the pyproject.toml or requirements.txt file.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no wheel, .venv should be ignored.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses pyproject.toml to manage dependencies. Locking is handled by poetry.lock.
#   It is generally recommended to commit poetry.lock.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM uses pyproject.toml to manage dependencies. Locking is handled by pdm.lock.
#   It is generally recommended to commit pdm.lock.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

